HTML
<!-- <!DOCTYPE html>  This is the code initial code segment that explain the HTML version. This is the 5th of version in the HTML -->



<head>  #### header part include the Meta data of the HTML file. 
    <title>The 1st try</title> ###  title is the part that name the browsers title bar. 
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css"> ### link is the way that that link the external CSS files to the HTML file
</head>



<body>  ### Body is the part that visible to the user. 

    <canvas id = "myCanvas"></canvas>

    <script src="main.js"></script>  ### This is the way to link the external JavaScript file to HTML 

</body>

css
body{
    margin: 0;
    background : darkgray ;
    overflow: hidden; ## This is very important because when we scrolling the window the window is going to too big
    text-align: center;
}